## 6. Styling approach

```
apps/storybook/.storybook/preview.css
  → @afenda/shadcn-studio/shadcn-default.css   (AdminCN :root / .dark)

Optional scoped theme layers:
  → @afenda/shadcn-studio/themes/swiss-noir.css
  → @afenda/shadcn-studio/themes/verdant-noir.css

apps/erp/src/app/globals.css
  → @afenda/shadcn-studio/shadcn-default.css   (production default)
```

**Methodology:** Tailwind v4 utility classes + CSS custom properties. No CSS Modules for shadcn primitives.

**Theme switching:** `next-themes` `class` strategy; themed surfaces use a scoped theme class wrapper + optional `.dark`.

**Responsive:** Tailwind breakpoints (`sm`, `lg`, `xl`, `2xl`); Storybook fullscreen layouts via `shadcnStudioFullscreenLayout`.

**Three palette series (Token Verification):**

1. AdminCN Light — `:root` from `shadcn-studio.css` (no wrapper class)
2. AdminCN Dark — `.dark` on panel wrapper only
3. Scoped theme dark — `.dark` + a governed theme class wrapper

**Hard stops (CSS authority):**

- **Never** copy `:root` / `.dark` token blocks into `storybook/*.css` — that creates drift (vibe-coding V011).
- **Never** put global `:root` or bare `.dark` overrides in theme CSS — use scoped classes only.
- **Never** add new semantic tokens to fix one Storybook story — use existing `--primary`, `--destructive`, etc.
- Side-by-side columns inherit from `html`; keep story `globals.theme: "light"` so AdminCN Light column reads `:root` SSOT.

